An Iyaganku Magistrates’ Court sitting in Ibadan on Tuesday, ordered that two men who allegedly abducted a housewife,  be remanded in a correctional facility, pending legal advice. The police charged Harande Tambaya, 34, and Umaru Abubakar, 35, with two counts of conspiracy and kidnapping. Magistrate O. Enilolobo, who did not take the plea of the defendants, ordered that they are remanded in the Nigerian Correctional Service in Agodi, pending legal advice from the office of the Director of Public Prosecutions. ALSO READ:Rape: 6-year old Nigerian 2emerges Africa’s youngest microsoft specialist Court sentences dry cleaner to 15 years in prison for… Applicant in court for attempting to steal car Court sentences mechanic to 10 months in prison for stealing… Five out of 10 kidnapped victims regain freedom in Osun She adjourned the matter until Sept . 30, for mention. The Prosecution Counsel, Sgt. Olalekan Adegbite told the court that the defendants and others at large allegedly committed the offence on July 1. Adegbite alleged that Harande and Umaru, abducted a housewife, Madam Foluke Akinrinde, 35, and demanded N25 million as ransom. The offence, he said, contravened the provisions of Section 3 (1) and (2) and punishable under Section 4 (1) of the Oyo State Kidnapping (Prohibition ) Law 2016. Here is how i overcome QUICK RELEASE and make it BIGGER, STRONGER And LONGER with this NAFDAC APPROVED NATURAL REMEDY. Click now!!